\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-simplex
\series default
: Convex hull of 
\begin_inset Formula $n+1$
\end_inset

 points 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{v}_{1},...,\boldsymbol{v}_{n+1}\in\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 We will use the letter 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 to denote a simplex, and we will denote the set of all possible 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-simplexes as 
\begin_inset Formula $S^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 The points 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{v}_{1},...,\boldsymbol{v}_{n+1}\in\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 are called the vertexes of the simplex.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Box Boxed
