\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
Polynomial curve
\series default
 
\series bold
of degree
\series default
 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 
\series bold
and dimension
\series default
 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

: Parametric curve 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{p}(t):=\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
p_{1}(t) & \cdots & p_{k}(t)\end{array}\right]^{T}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}(t)$
\end_inset

 is a polynomial of degree 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
p_{i}(t)=\sum_{j=0}^{n}p_{i,j}t^{j}=\boldsymbol{p}_{i}^{T}\boldsymbol{t},\qquad c_{i,j}\in\mathbb{R},t\in\mathbb{R}
\]

\end_inset

In this paper, we will use the polynomial curves of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $k=n$
\end_inset

 and we will refer to them simply as 
\begin_inset Formula $n-$
\end_inset

th order polyomial curve.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{t}:=\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
t^{n} & t^{n-1}\cdots & 1\end{array}\right]^{T}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let us also define the permutation matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $P=\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
0 & \cdots & 0 & 1\\
0 & \cdots & 1 & 0\\
\vdots & \iddots & \vdots & \vdots\\
1 & 0 & 0 & 0
\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Problem definition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This project investigate the following problem:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Box Boxed
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
inner_pos "t"
use_parbox 0
use_makebox 0
